# Platform self-heal (APK bundled)

Every Solar APK ships a **platform repair kit** under `app/src/main/assets/platform/`:

- Production Xposed modules (context bridge Y1/Y2, theme font, Rockbox IME/compat hooks)
- Dalvik Xposed framework vendor trees (api17 + api19)
- Init hooks (`99XposedInit.sh`)
- **Deprecated artifact cleanup** — legacy `/system/app/SolarContextBridge*.apk` and wrong-family bridges

**Not included (2026-07-19):** org.rockbox APK/libs or JJ (`com.themoon.y1`) install. Solar does not self-heal third-party launchers — launch-if-present only when already on the device. Y1 ROM may still bake Rockbox; Y2 default ROM strips it.

## Upgrade contract

A user on the **first ever Solar release** who installs the **current APK** (OTA or adb) should reach the same **Solar + Xposed** platform goals as a fresh ROM flash, when **root is available**:

1. **Silent background prep** runs once per `manifest.prepVersion` bump — no blocking wizard on boot for ROM-ready devices
2. Ladder: deprecated cleanup → Xposed framework → module install → enable (no Rockbox/JJ install step)
3. **Rockbox behavior when present** is **Xposed hooks** (`SolarRockboxIme`, context-bridge policy) — not APK staging of `org.rockbox`
4. Graceful fallback without root — Solar music/settings still work
5. **Blocking wizard** is manual-only (Settings repair); do not re-gate on probe gaps after prep applied (caused loops)

## When editing platform prep

- Bump `prepVersion` in `sync-platform-assets.sh` when ladder steps or deprecated list changes
- Add new deprecated rows to `manifest.json` via sync script — never leave stale `/system` APKs from old releases
- Wizard keys must use `Y1InputKeys` / `PlatformPrepWizardKeys` — not stock Android focus/touch
- ROM zips remain canonical for fresh flashes; APK self-heal closes OTA/adb drift gaps for Solar/Xposed only

See: `solar-rom/patches/rockbox/README.md`, `platform/` Java package, `sync-platform-assets.sh`.
